The course introduces contemporary influencing and manipulation trends in digital environments. The participants learn intervention practices used to cope with information disorders to increase information resilience in society and community. This is a practical course that uses interactive student-centred learning methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Information disorders and manipulations are increasingly frequent in professional communication work and in the individual's everyday information consumption. The course provides evidence-based intervention practices for preventing the dissemination of disinformation in public communication. The course offers various practical guidelines and social media analysis on the organisational and individual levels.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, the student:
*	Knows the communicative principles and narratives of how information disorders are disseminated on individual and organisational levels,
*	In the unexpected critical information situation is able to plan and execute communication drawing from the communicative needs of the community,
*	Understands the social and psychical tensions that arise in infodemic situations and is able to use communicative practices to alleviate the tensions in the organisation and community.
